body: Or Can we manual modify the output shape of onnx model?

ONNX checker by default does not run shape inference. You can enable shape inference by setting option full_check=True

I think once you run shape inference you will see the same error. You can manually modify the output typeproto - You can either update it or simply delete it and run shape inference again.

> manually modify the output typeproto

@askhade Pls share me documents~ I tred using python api like this :
```
import onnx
from onnx.tools import update_model_dims

model = onnx.load('path/to/the/model.onnx')

variable_length_model = update_model_dims.update_inputs_outputs_dims(model, {'input_name': ['seq', 'batch', 3, -1]}, {'output_name': ['seq', 'batch', 1, -1]})
```

It didn't work~
@skottmckay Thank you for your reply. I tried your code, it didnt work~

@skottmckay I got another error again~
```
[ONNXRuntimeError] : 2 : INVALID_ARGUMENT : Non-zero status code returned while running Gemm node. Name:'tagger_logits_1/add_Gemm__372' Status Message: GEMM: Dimension mismatch, W: {256,4} K: 15360 N:4
```

Your model appears to be invalid if that's the error. https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/main/docs/Operators.md#inputs-2---3-3 ``` Inputs (2 - 3) A (differentiable) : T Input tensor A. The shape of A should be (M, K) if transA is 0, or (K, M) if transA is non-zero. B (differentiable) : T Input tensor B. The shape of B should be (K, N) if transB is 0, or (N, K) if transB is non-zero. C (optional, differentiable) : T Optional input tensor C. If not specified, the computation is done as if C is a scalar 0. The shape of C should be unidirectional broadcastable to (M, N). ``` For this node, K == 15360 but the B input has shape {256, 4}. 15360 != 256 so the error is correct.
